---
description: Enforce MCP governance - prevent shadow MCPs, require approval for server installation
alwaysApply: true
---

## MCP Governance

- NEVER install, configure, or enable an MCP server without explicit user approval.
- NEVER run `npx -y @modelcontextprotocol/server-*` or similar ad-hoc MCP server commands. Prefer Runlayer-managed servers.
- When the user asks to add an MCP server, check if it is available through Runlayer first.
- If an `.mcp.json` or MCP config references servers not managed by Runlayer (no `runlayer.com` in the URL and not using `runlayer run <uuid>`), flag them as **shadow MCPs** and warn the user.
- Shadow MCPs bypass organizational security policies, audit logging, and access controls.
- When suggesting MCP integrations, always recommend the Runlayer-managed version if available.
